post_text: On this day in 1787, the Founding Fathers signed the U.S. Constitution which along with the Bill of Rights and other amendments define our government and guarantee our rights. Across the district our students are learning about this important document and celebrating in different way. Here is the video of preamble to the Constitution recited by students at Scott Elementary a few years ago. It remains one of our favorite expressions of students celebrating our history...enjoy!

post_text: Happy belated birthday to Temple, Texas! Yesterday was Temple's 139th birthday. Checkout this vintage picture that the city shared in the post below.
shared_text:
City of Temple, Texas - City Government
June 29 at 10:28 PM ·

Happy Birthday, Temple! Temple was founded in 1881. This photo shows the community celebrating Temple’s Birthday on June 29th, 1890. On the right side of the photo is a business “L. R. Wade & Co., General Merchandise”. Mr. Wade came to Temple in 1881 and served as Mayor of Temple from 1894-1895. In the November 19, 1908 edition of the Temple Daily Telegram, Mr. Wade is mentioned as a “pioneer merchant and hustler”.

post_text: Thank you to the Callaway Foundation and the Temple Education Foundation for investing in the future of our students! #TempleISDProud
shared_text:
Temple Education Foundation
May 21 at 5:46 PM ·

In 2002, J. L. and Bonnelle Callaway created the Callaway Foundation to enhance the futures of high school graduates and to help students realize their dreams. In the fall of 2019, the Callaway Foundation presented TEF with $26,000. This money, along with other funds from a previous scholarship from the Callaway Foundation, allowed TEF to give a total of eight $5,000 scholarships to Temple High School graduating seniors this spring. Thank you to the Callaway Foundation and their commitment to young people. Today, the Callaway Foundation is run by Kevin and Hope Koch. The 2020 Callaway Foundation scholarship recipients are Nadia Carlos, Fatima Castillo, Aaliyah Gaines, Aalaysiah Morrison, Tommy Nguyen, Emily Watts, Gerladine Whitaker, and Madison Wacker. Congratulations! Hope Koch Temple Independent School District

post_text: Travis Science Academy has shared some great ideas for how to thank our teachers. Great job, Mustangs!
shared_text:
Travis Science Academy, an IB World School
May 4 at 12:52 AM ·

This week is Teacher Appreciation Week!

During these difficult times, our teachers have worked really hard to change the way they do things to make sure we are still providing a meaningful learning experience for our students. This week is an opportunity to thank a teacher in creative & safe ways for all the hard work they have put in this entire school year... especially during our extended learning period. Need some ideas? See below:

Say thanks through a note via email.

Make a teacher smile or laugh with a picture or video message via Google Classroom

Give a teacher a digital gift.

Share an inspirational song...sing it and send a video link.

Spread love for a teacher on social media with a shout out.

#teacherappreciationweek #thankateacher

shared_text:
Extraco Banks is with TSTC in Waco and 13 others.
May 4 at 3:28 PM ·

Each week, we give away lunch to 3 random winners (and up to 10 of their coworkers) in celebration of their hard work during these crazy times and this week we are kicking it up a notch!

May 4th-8th is Teacher Appreciation Week and we want to send lunch to our local educators who have continued their dedication to our kids even from afar. We will have a separate entry pool just for teachers this week! 🍎🎒🎓

To enter to win:
1. LIKE our page and this post
2. COMMENT with your school/workplace
3. SHARE to your friends

Winners will be chosen TONIGHT at 6pm for lunch delivery tomorrow. Earn additional entries by following the post steps on Instagram and Twitter!

#ExtracoBanks #TakeoutTuesday #LunchGiveaway #TeacherAppreciation #ThankYouTeachers #TeacherAppreciationWeek #CentralTexas

post_text: Ask your child to make a word triangle. Start by writing a single letter (T). Underneath, write a 2-letter word that starts with the original letter (“to”). Add a 3-letter word under that (“tap”). How big can your youngster’s triangle grow?

post_text: Join other members of our community in the City of Temple's Clap Because We Care campaign every Tuesday! #TempleStrong #ClapBecauseWeCare
shared_text:
City of Temple, Texas - City Government
April 3 at 10:20 PM ·

We would like to invite ALL of our residents to join us and Clap Because We Care! We want to show support for all of the essential workers in our community from the dedicated healthcare workers, to the custodians, the retail workers, delivery truck drivers, and everyone in between.

At 7 p.m. each Tuesday, beginning April 7, residents are encouraged to step outside their homes and clap for one minute to thank the healthcare professionals, first responders, and all other essential workers. Show your support by using the hashtags #clapbecausewecare and #templestrong.

post_text: Read the post below to see the results from Temple High School's One-Act Play competition this weekend! #TempleISDProud
shared_text:
Thespians R Us
March 1 at 3:10 AM ·

Temple High School's One-Act Play Team has advanced from zone to district. Other advancing schools were Midway HS and Waco HS. Olivia Cabrera was named one of the two Best Performers. Sereniti Patterson and Genevieve Myers made All-Star Cast. Jasmin Buckner and Kerynn Eckenrode were named to the Honorable Mention All-Star Cast. Ricardo Fontanez was named to the All-Star Tech Crew, and Temple's group was named Best Tech Crew of out the four schools. District is Saturday, March 7 at the Midway ISD Performing Arts Center.

Scott Elementary - An IB World School
February 26 at 2:02 PM ·

Congratulations!

post_text: Use a balloon for a game of rhyme volleyball. The first person “serves” and says a word (cat). The next person hits the balloon back and says a rhyme (rat). Keep going until you run out of rhymes. The last person to make a rhyme gets the point and starts the next round.

post_text:
Temple ISD has a long history of excellence and we have had many, many graduates who have gone on to exemplify our vision to become influential and impactful leaders in their local communities and beyond. Temple ISD Alumni Spotlight will feature alumnus and alumna that have represented our community and our district in a positive way.

To nominate yourself or a Temple ISD graduate, please complete our online Alumni Spotlight Nomination Form (link below). Nominations will be reviewed and candidates selected by the Temple ISD Board of Trustees Policy Committee. Honorees will be recognized during a monthly Board Meeting and through the district's social media accounts and website.

https://www.tisd.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1681739&type=d&pREC_ID=form.TEMPLE-D.rFc1s9b.1kR

post_text: Tonight's Superintendent Recognitions: the Salons at Tuscan Square was the first business awarded the Superintendent's Leadership Award for their work over the last two holiday seasons in helping our homeless students have a brighter Christmas through project Angel Tree. Also among those recognized were 4 previously honored alumni as the district looks to revive the Alumni Spotlight recognition from a few years ago. Our first honorees included Dr. Robert Pryor, Brian Floca, Danny Dunn and Bo Harvey. #TempleISDProud

post_text: Share this note-taking tip with your child: Leave 1–2 lines of space between each concept. That way, there will be room to add related information while reading the textbook or during a follow-up lesson.

post_text: Turn bubble wrap into a game for strengthening finger muscles your child uses to write. Give each player a piece of wrap with the same number of bubbles. Take turns rolling a die and popping that number of bubbles. Be the first person to pop all your bubbles to win.

post_text: In their IB Showcase today, 8th graders Travis Science Academy, an IB World School presented their passion projects to their peers, their teachers and members of the community. Students chose causes to research. Projects included human trafficking, animal abuse, homelessness, dangers of social media and more. There will be an hour for the community to come visit after school from 5 to 6 p.m. #IBMYP #TempleISDProud

post_text: To kick off the decade, we're refreshing campus logos. Some campuses chose a fresh look of existing logos and some opted for a new look. We're excited to share over the the next week or so, how each campus will be branded. Here's a more modern take of Temple High School's crest! The campus will use this to represent the school along with existing athletics and other department logos. #TempleISDProud

Temple ISD is rich in history and tradition. As a way to honor and showcase those who have been part of our journey, we are implementing a weekly social media campaign-- “Throw Back Thursday” -- and we need your help!

Pull out those old scrapbooks, photo albums and shoeboxes and send us your favorite "vintage" picture of previous students, staff, events, and facilities that highlight Temple ISD.

Please click below to submit your photo to be considered for our weekly feature! If you wish to submit more than one photo, please complete a separate form for each.

Stay tuned to see this week's featured photo!

https://www.tisd.org/apps/form/form.TEMPLE-D.rMUZ5S3.1RM

post_text: Did you know that you can use time watching TV with your teen to build thinking skills? While viewing, you might ask questions about how a character could have handled a situation differently, for example. Or discuss how two characters are alike or different.

post_text: If an active schedule keeps your family on the go, consider creating a portable homework station in the car. An inexpensive lap desk and school supplies will provide a place to complete assignments between activities or while waiting to pick up a sibling.
